&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Objective&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Reporting to the Director/VP, Talent Acquisition and Management, this role owns the administration of US benefits programs, payroll coordination, and wellness initiatives, while also contributing to recruitment efforts and supporting broader Talent operations across the employee lifecycle.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This person is a critical connector — keeping benefits running smoothly, payroll accurate, and employee experience programs active, while stepping into recruiting support as the team’s needs require.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you will do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits Administration&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; Serve as day-to-day administrator for all US benefits programs including health, dental, vision, FSA, 401(k), and voluntary benefits&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; Manage open enrollment end-to-end: communications, employee support, vendor coordination, and system updates&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; Administer leave programs (FMLA, ADA accommodations, state leave, parental leave, disability) in compliance with applicable federal, state, and local regulations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; Maintain benefits vendor relationships and support annual renewal process in partnership with the Director/VP&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; Respond to employee benefits inquiries promptly and accurately; serve as the first point of contact for benefits questions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
