&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a motivated and detail-oriented trainee or student to join our finance team in our Luxembourg office near Cloche d’Or. This is a versatile role designed to give you hands-on experience in a fast-paced environment. Whether you are looking for a mandatory internship or a summer student job to complement your studies, we offer the opportunity to learn in an international environment with a great team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you will do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will work closely with our Accounting Manager on a variety of missions, including:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Period-End Closings: Assisting with monthly and quarterly closing processes (clôtures) and ensuring data accuracy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Financial Analysis: Supporting the preparation of reports.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cash Management: Helping with daily treasury tasks, bank booking and bank reconciliations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Accounting Support: Assisting with invoice processing, expense reports, and general ledger maintenance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Skills&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Currently enrolled in a Bachelor’s or Master’s degree in Accounting or Finance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A strong command of Excel (vlookups, pivot tables) is essential. Familiarity with accounting software is a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fluency in English is required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are organized, curious, and not afraid to dive into the numbers. You have a &quot;can-do&quot; attitude and enjoy working in a team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

