&lt;h3&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our Purpose&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;P\S\L Group is a global organisation dedicated to putting information at the service of medicine. The companies and people of the P\S\L Group aim to improve medical care by serving those who need it, those who provide it and those who seek to improve it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our primary purpose is to help clients increase the effectiveness of activities pertaining to scientific communication, medical education and product/service marketing. To this end, we want our information services to contribute to the goals we share with our clients, namely: to accelerate the advancement of medicine and help people enjoy better, longer lives.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About PeerVoice&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;A part of P\S\L Group, &lt;/span&gt;PeerVoice provides evidence-based medical education to healthcare professionals most in need of the knowledge, skills, and competence imparted by the education. Our mission is to facilitate the creation and distribution of clinically important medical education, to ensure access to the education by need-to-know clinicians, and to measure the outcomes and impact of the education. PeerVoice achieves this mission through our expertise in identifying gaps in education, content development, faculty selection, outcomes assessment, production and distribution for a variety of medical education formats (i.e, e-learning, video, and print).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We believe in the development of innovative products and services that leverage at least one of our Group’s key assets in order to offer our clients a differentiated value proposition and build a sustainable competitive advantage.&amp;nbsp; In addition, we believe that our individual target markets have special dynamics and circumstances which require market-specific expertise as well as influence in terms of how these products and services are launched and then enhanced over time.&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our innovative, on-demand multichannel education solutions drive behaviour change in professionals and improve patient outcomes. They feature concise content designs and key thought leaders delivering the most relevant science. All our OLA and CME activities adhere to the rigorous guidelines set forth for independent medical education.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We publish medical education across a wide swath of medical specialties, including:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cardiology&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dermatology&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Gastroenterology&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;General and Family Practice&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hematology&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Neurology&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oncology&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ophthalmology&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Psychiatry&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Respirology&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Rheumatology&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Urology&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;em&gt;Objective&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;The Medical Director will collaborate with internal and external experts to complete the following key tasks:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify existing practice gaps and underlying unmet needs (15%)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop strategic needs assessments/proposals that align these practice gaps and unmet needs with innovative solutions to address these needs (20%)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create high-quality content for medical education activities that meet established timelines, specifications, and budgets (65%)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;em&gt;What you will do&lt;/em&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain knowledge of the rules and regulations that govern independent medical education and continuing professional development (both accredited and non-accredited)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain knowledge of important clinical issue

